lenders.loan_because: I believe that the empowerment of women, gender equality, and education will end poverty and world hunger.
lenders.occupational_info:
Currently, I am traveling the world with my life partner, Alex. We have been traveling for over 6 months having visited the West coast of Canada, Hawaii, New Zealand, Indonesia and currently in Australia. 

At my last place of employment, I worked as a consultant for an Employee Assistance Program for 8 years, which provided counseling services to individuals and families in need of emotional support. My educational background specialized in Social services and sociology. Also, I spent over 2 years volunteering with the Canadian Red Cross in disaster management. I worked with a large team who helped individuals in my community who lost their homes in a personal fire or whose lives were affected by a natural disaster such as a tornado or a flood. I have witnessed firsthand the effects of poverty and hunger in Asia, Africa and South America. I have had the opportunity of working with individuals living in LDCs and can attest the power of micro-credit and self-empowerment of women.

I am passionate about helping others and I intend to work in international development/human rights. For now, I am grateful for being a part of the Kiva Community and doing what I can while traveling abroad. Together, I believe, we can all make a positive difference in the world as we are all connected.

lenders.occupational_info:
Dear Madam / Sir

Namaskar

I take this opportunity first to introduce my organisation samajik shaikshanik vikas kendra (SSVK) and its activities since 26 yrs. We are a grassroots organisation operating in one of the most poverty endemic pockets spread over five districts Madhubani, Darbhanga, Madhepura,Saharsa and Supaul of North Bihar ( India). We primarily work with below poverty line Mushar families(Sheduled Caste) who constitute the lowliest of the low even among the dalits.   In addition commitment also lies with other below poverty line groups coming from other scheduled caste groups and depressed backward classes from other districts of Bihar and Jharkhand.  The organisation stands committed to the effective empowerment of its socially, politically and economically marginalised target group. For further details, you can visit us at our website: www.ssvk.org

 To complete our projects and commitment, we welcome your financial as well as other resources. All donations/contributions to SSVK India will be eligible to tax exemption under Section 80G of the Income Tax Act. SSVK receives Foreign Donation through our Foreign Contribution Regulation Act (FCRA).
